- It goes through the real native path: TS test script builds the napi binding before tests (`src/ts/package.json:23`), the wrapper delegates to native (`src/ts/src/index.ts:721`), and napi forwards to `engine.consolidate_with_provider` (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:1105`).
- Allowlist reconciliation is in the shared source of truth, with both snake/camel forms adjacent to the existing ingest precedent (`src/conformance/governed-surface-allowlist.json:14`). This is the right classification: consolidate is a state-mutating application command, not instrumentation.
- No regression spotted to recovery/core/read governance: core and recovery denylist are unchanged (`src/conformance/governed-surface-allowlist.json:24`), read members are unchanged (`src/conformance/governed-surface-allowlist.json:9`), and both TS/Python suites still load the same allowlist and enforce subset/read/recovery assertions.

I did not run tests or `git diff` because the sandbox is read-only and git metadata lives outside the readable workspace; review was from the checked-out files and requested context.
